---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { BOOK_TITLE, BOOK_SUBTITLE, AUTHOR, AMAZON_URL } from '../consts.js';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="The Book"
  description={`About ${BOOK_TITLE}: ${BOOK_SUBTITLE}.`}
>
  <section class="bg-cream">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-4 py-16 md:py-24 grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-start">
      <!-- Cover -->
      <div class="md:sticky md:top-28">
        <img
          src="/book-cover.jpg"
          alt={`Cover of ${BOOK_TITLE} by ${AUTHOR}`}
          width="800"
          height="1200"
          class="aspect-[2/3] w-full max-w-sm mx-auto rounded-md shadow-2xl object-cover"
        />

        <div class="mt-6 flex flex-col gap-2 max-w-sm mx-auto">
          <a
            href={AMAZON_URL}
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="block text-center rounded-md bg-gold text-navy font-semibold px-5 py-3 hover:bg-navy hover:text-cream no-underline transition-colors"
          >
            Buy on Amazon
          </a>
          <a
            href="/contact"
            class="block text-center rounded-md border border-navy text-navy px-5 py-3 hover:bg-navy hover:text-cream no-underline transition-colors"
          >
            Bulk orders &amp; signed copies
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Description -->
      <div>
        <p class="text-gold uppercase tracking-widest text-sm font-semibold mb-3">About the book</p>
        <h1 class="font-heading text-4xl md:text-5xl text-navy mb-2">{BOOK_TITLE}</h1>
        <p class="font-heading text-xl md:text-2xl text-ink/80 italic mb-8">{BOOK_SUBTITLE}</p>

        <div class="prose">
          <p>
            <em>Learning to Walk with Him</em> tells the unvarnished story of a young missionary
            who showed up scared, distracted, and reluctant — and slowly learned that
            discipleship is less about being impressive and more about staying close.
          </p>
          <p>
            Ken Smith weaves personal mission stories with scripture, prayer, and the practical
            disciplines of a life of faith. Each lesson is a doorway:
          </p>

          <h3>Inside the book</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Lesson 1</strong> — You never know who you will touch.</li>
            <li><strong>Lesson 2</strong> — You are sent where you are sent for a reason.</li>
            <li><strong>Lesson 3</strong> — Keep the Savior's life and ministry as the focus in all you do.</li>
            <li><strong>Lesson 4</strong> — Don't underestimate the power of prayer and the Lord's love for you.</li>
            <li><strong>Lesson 5</strong> — Baptisms aren't the focus; the Savior's love is.</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>From <em>Learning to Walk with Him</em></h3>
          <blockquote>
            "God doesn't waste anyone's willingness to try."
            <br /><span class="text-sm"><em>Learning to Walk with Him</em></span>
          </blockquote>
          <blockquote>
            "When you make the Savior the center of your mission instead of yourself, your mission becomes what it was meant to be."
            <br /><span class="text-sm"><em>Learning to Walk with Him</em></span>
          </blockquote>

          <h3>Details</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Format: Paperback, eBook</li>
            <li>Pages: 153</li>
            <li>Publisher: Walking with Him Publishing</li>
            <li>ISBN (paperback): 979-8-9956806-0-4</li>
            <li>ISBN (eBook): 979-8-9956806-1-1</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
